"Rule sensitivity","value":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules.","warning":true},{"label":"Key authority","value":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"label":"After approval","value":"Applicant may work for most employers in Canada subject to printed conditions. Review expiry alignment with principal applicant status."}],"eligibility":[{"criterion":"Principal applicant has clear Canadian pathway or status plan","met":true},{"criterion":"Genuine temporary purpose for visit documented","met":true},{"criterion":"Strong ties to home country demonstrated","met":true},{"criterion":"Funds for visit and return travel","met":true},{"criterion":"Relationship to principal applicant proven","met":true},{"criterion":"No undeclared refusals or inadmissibility","met":true}],"redFlagsBanner":"Most weak spouse/dependent OWP files fail because the principal applicant does not qualify, the relationship proof is thin, or prior refusals are not addressed.","redFlags":[{"title":"Principal applicant not eligible","description":"Principal worker, student, or PR applicant category does not support dependant OWP.","fix":"Verify current IRCC category before taking full file; assess visitor or other status options","severity":"High"},{"title":"Weak relationship proof","description":"Marriage certificate only, limited photos, no communication, or no shared life evidence.","fix":"Add relationship timeline, photos, chats, travel, financial, and family evidence","severity":"Very common"},{"title":"Recent marriage before filing","description":"Marriage occurred shortly before application with limited relationship history.","fix":"Prepare detailed relationship narrative and third-party corroboration","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Prior refusals not disclosed","description":"Applicant or principal has previous Canada or other country refusals omitted from forms.","fix":"Disclose all refusals and address changed circumstances","severity":"High"},{"title":"Principal status expiring soon","description":"Principal permit expires shortly, limiting dependant permit duration or eligibility.","fix":"Coordinate principal extension or wait for renewed status where strategic","severity":"Common"},{"title":"Insufficient funds","description":"Family cannot show credible support for living costs in Canada.","fix":"Add bank history, employment income, pay stubs, and sponsor explanation","severity":"Medium"},{"title":"Inconsistent forms","description":"Dates, addresses, marital status, or family details conflict across forms.","fix":"Run consistency review against passport, marriage, and prior applications","severity":"Common"}],"faqs":[{"q":"Can every spouse of a student get an open work permit?","a":"No. Eligibility depends on current IRCC rules, the student''s program and institution, and other conditions."},{"q":"Can every spouse of a worker get an open work permit?","a":"No. The principal worker''s occupation, permit type, and status must qualify under current policy."},{"q":"Is a marriage certificate enough?","a":"Usually not by itself. Provide relationship history, photos, communication, travel, financial ties, and family evidence where available."},{"q":"Can common-law partners apply?","a":"Yes, if they meet IRCC''s common-law definition and can prove cohabitation and genuine relationship."},{"q":"Can dependent children get open work permits?","a":"Only in limited circumstances. Many children need visitor or study status instead. Screen age and dependency rules carefully."},{"q":"Should the application be filed together with the principal applicant?","a":"Sometimes. It depends on timing, principal eligibility, documents, and risk. Joint filing can help context but is not always best."},{"q":"How long will the OWP be valid?","a":"Often tied to the principal applicant''s status and passport validity. IRCC decides the final duration."},{"q":"Can the applicant work while waiting?","a":"Only if they already have authorization and meet maintained status rules. Outside-Canada applicants cannot work until approved and admitted with proper status."},{"q":"What if there was a previous spouse OWP refusal?","a":"Order notes if useful, address refusal reasons directly, and strengthen principal eligibility and relationship evidence."},{"q":"Does approval lead to PR?","a":"No. OWP is temporary status. It may support Canadian work experience, but PR requires a separate pathway."},{"q":"What is Description for this service?","a":"Open work permit pathway for eligible spouses, common-law partners, or qualifying dependants linked to a principal applicant''s Canadian work, study, or immigration status."},{"q":"What is Eligible applicants for this service?","a":"Genuine spouse/common-law partner or eligible dependant · Principal applicant has qualifying status · Relationship documents · Funds and admissibility evidence"},{"q":"What is Rule sensitivity for this service?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"Important note on Rule sensitivity?","a":"Eligibility for spouses of students and workers depends on current IRCC categories, program level, occupation, and principal status. Always verify current rules."},{"q":"What is Key authority for this service?","a":"Immigration, Refugees and Citizenship Canada (IRCC)"},{"q":"What is After approval for this service?","a":"Applicant may work for most employers in Canada subject to printed conditions. Review expiry alignment with principal applicant status."},{"q":"Is Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway required?","a":"Principal applicant has valid qualifying status in Canada or approved pathway is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying dependant under IRCC rules required?","a":"Applicant is spouse, common-law partner, or qualifying dependant under IRCC rules is typically required."},{"q":"Is Relationship is genuine and well documented required?","a":"Marriage certificate alone may not be enough"},{"q":"Is Principal worker occupation, employer, or permit category qualifies where required required?","a":"Principal worker occupation, employer, or permit category qualifies where required is typically required."},{"q":"Is Principal student program and institution qualify where required required?","a":"Principal student program and institution qualify where required is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant passport valid for requested permit period required?","a":"Applicant passport valid for requested permit period is typically required."},{"q":"Is Applicant has no inadmissibility, misrepresentation, or undisclosed refusal issue required?","a":"Applicant has no inadmissibility, misrepresentation, or undisclosed refusal issue is typically required."},{"q":"Is Funds or family support evidence available for settlement and stay required?","a":"Funds or family support evidence available for settlement and stay is typically required."},{"q":"Is Medical exam or biometrics completed if required required?","a":"Assess whether Medical exam or biometrics completed if required is satisfied for this case."},{"q":"What is the Processing time?","a":"3–5m — Varies by applicant location"},{"q":"What is the Government fee?","a":"CAD $255 — Verify on canada.ca"},{"q":"What is the Our approval rate?","a":"88% — ~76% benchmark"},{"q":"What is the Required docs?","a":"13 — + relationship proof"},{"q":"What is the Consultancy fee?","a":"See fee tab — + govt only"}],"compliance":["Client service agreement and consent must be on file before submission","Never guarantee open work permit approval or work rights before authorization","Confirm paid representation authority for Canadian immigration filings","Fee quotes must separate c